<tr id="L310"><td><a href="#L310">310</a></td><td>KARIDIAN:  Kodos, whoever he was</td></tr>

<tr id="L311"><td><a href="#L311">311</a></td><td>KIRK:  Or is.</td></tr>

<tr id="L312"><td><a href="#L312">312</a></td><td>KARIDIAN:  Or is. Kodos made a decision of life and death. Some had to die that others might live. You're a man of decision, Captain. You ought to understand that.</td></tr>

<tr id="L313"><td><a href="#L313">313</a></td><td>KIRK:  All I understand is that four thousand people were needlessly butchered.</td></tr>

<tr id="L314"><td><a href="#L314">314</a></td><td>KARIDIAN:  In order to save four thousand others. And if the supply ships hadn't come earlier than expected, this Kodos of yours might have gone down in history as a great hero.</td></tr>

<tr id="L315"><td><a href="#L315">315</a></td><td>KIRK:  But he didn't. And history has made its judgment.</td></tr>

<tr id="L316"><td><a href="#L316">316</a></td><td>KARIDIAN:  If you're so sure that I'm Kodos, why not kill me now? Let bloody vengeance take its final course! And see what difference it makes to this universe of yours.</td></tr>

<tr id="L317"><td><a href="#L317">317</a></td><td>KIRK:  Those beautiful words, well acted, change nothing.</td></tr>

<tr id="L318"><td><a href="#L318">318</a></td><td>KARIDIAN:  I suppose not. They're merely tools, like this ship of yours.</td></tr>

<tr id="L319"><td><a href="#L319">319</a></td><td>KIRK:  There are no previous records to Anton Karidian prior to twenty years ago.</td></tr>

<tr id="L320"><td><a href="#L320">320</a></td><td>KARIDIAN:  Blood thins. The body fails. One is finally grateful for a failing memory. I no longer treasure life, not even my own. I am tired! And the past is a blank. Did you get everything you, wanted, Captain Kirk?</td></tr>

<tr id="L321"><td><a href="#L321">321</a></td><td>KIRK:  If I had gotten everything I wanted, you might not walk out of this room alive.</td></tr>

<tr id="L322"><td><a href="#L322">322</a></td><td>LENORE:  Captain Kirk.</td></tr>

<tr id="L323"><td><a href="#L323">323</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: She enters from the next room</td></tr>

<tr id="L324"><td><a href="#L324">324</a></td><td>LENORE:  (to Karidian) You'd better rest now. There's a stain of cruelty on your shining armour, Captain. You could have spared him, and me. You talked of using tools. I was a tool, wasn't l? A tool to use against my father.</td></tr>

<tr id="L325"><td><a href="#L325">325</a></td><td>KIRK:  In the beginning perhaps. But later, I wanted it to be more than that.</td></tr>

<tr id="L326"><td><a href="#L326">326</a></td><td>LENORE:  Later. Everything's always later. Later. Latest. Too late. Too late, Captain. You are like your ship, powerful, and not human. There is no mercy in you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L327"><td><a href="#L327">327</a></td><td>KIRK:  If he is Kodos, then I've shown him more mercy than he deserves. And if he isn't, then we'll let you off at Benecia, and no harm done.</td></tr>

<tr id="L328"><td><a href="#L328">328</a></td><td>LENORE:  Captain Kirk. Who are you to say what harm was done?</td></tr>

<tr id="L329"><td><a href="#L329">329</a></td><td>KIRK:  Who do I have to be?</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Sickbay</td></tr>
<tr id="L330"><td><a href="#L330">330</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Kevin is pacing up and down in the background, overhearing what is being dictated</td></tr>

<tr id="L331"><td><a href="#L331">331</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Medical log. Lieutenant Riley's sufficiently recovered to be discharged, but the Captain's ordered him restricted to Sickbay to prevent contact with the passenger who calls himself Karidian and who's suspected of being Kodos the Executioner and of murdering the Lieutenant's family.</td></tr>

<tr id="L332"><td><a href="#L332">332</a></td><td>SOMEONE: Captain's log, stardate 2819.8. Suspect under surveillance. Strategic areas under double guard. Performance of the Karidian Players taking place as scheduled.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Ship's Theatre</td></tr>
<tr id="L333"><td><a href="#L333">333</a></td><td>LENORE:  (on stage) Tonight, the Karidian Players present Hamlet, another in a series of living plays presented in space, dedicated to the tradition of classic theatre. Hamlet is a violent play about violent times when life was cheap and ambition was God.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Kirk's quarters</td></tr>
