<tr id="L375"><td><a href="#L375">375</a></td><td>LENORE:  We'll be ready. Don't you see? All the ghosts are dead. I've buried them. There's no more blood on your hands.</td></tr>

<tr id="L376"><td><a href="#L376">376</a></td><td>KARIDIAN:  Oh, my child, my child. You've left me nothing! You were the one thing in my life untouched by what I'd done.</td></tr>

<tr id="L377"><td><a href="#L377">377</a></td><td>LENORE:  But you're safe now, Father. I've saved you. Now, no one can touch you. Not even Captain Kirk. See Caesar come? He's awed by your greatness, your shining brightness. Bright as a blade before it is stained with blood.</td></tr>

<tr id="L378"><td><a href="#L378">378</a></td><td>KIRK:  Bright as a blade. Come with me, both of you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L379"><td><a href="#L379">379</a></td><td>LENORE:  Of course. After the play.</td></tr>

<tr id="L380"><td><a href="#L380">380</a></td><td>KIRK:  The play is over. It's been over for twenty years.</td></tr>

<tr id="L381"><td><a href="#L381">381</a></td><td>KARIDIAN:  I was a soldier in a cause. There were things to be done, terrible things.</td></tr>

<tr id="L382"><td><a href="#L382">382</a></td><td>LENORE:  Stop it, Father! You have nothing to justify.</td></tr>

<tr id="L383"><td><a href="#L383">383</a></td><td>KARIDIAN:  Murder, flight, suicide, madness. I never wanted the blood on my hands ever to stain you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L384"><td><a href="#L384">384</a></td><td>LENORE:  I did it for you. I've saved you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L385"><td><a href="#L385">385</a></td><td>KIRK:  By killing seven innocent men.</td></tr>

<tr id="L386"><td><a href="#L386">386</a></td><td>LENORE:  They weren't innocent! They were dangerous! I would have killed a world to save him!</td></tr>

<tr id="L387"><td><a href="#L387">387</a></td><td>STAGEHAND [OC]:  Curtain going up, one minute.</td></tr>

<tr id="L388"><td><a href="#L388">388</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Kirk takes Karidian's arm</td></tr>

<tr id="L389"><td><a href="#L389">389</a></td><td>LENORE:  The play, Captain. He must go on. This is the great Karidian.</td></tr>

