<tr id="L395"><td><a href="#L395">395</a></td><td>LENORE:  It will become a floating tomb, drifting through space with the soul of the great Karidian giving performances at every star he touches. (Kirk moves towards her) I know how to use this, Captain.</td></tr>

<tr id="L396"><td><a href="#L396">396</a></td><td>KARIDIAN:  No.</td></tr>

<tr id="L397"><td><a href="#L397">397</a></td><td>LENORE:  Caesar, beware the ides of March.</td></tr>

<tr id="L398"><td><a href="#L398">398</a></td><td>KARIDIAN:  No, child! Don't!</td></tr>

<tr id="L399"><td><a href="#L399">399</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: As she squeezes the trigger, her father steps in front of Kirk, and takes the shot himself. Lenore screams at what she has done. and Kirk takes the phaser from her as she kneels over Karidian's body</td></tr>

<tr id="L400"><td><a href="#L400">400</a></td><td>LENORE:  Father. Father! O, proud, death! What feast is toward in thine eternal cell, that thou, such a prince at a shot so bloodily hast struck? The curtain, the curtain rises. It rises. There's no time to sleep. The play. The play. The play's the thing, wherein we'll catch the conscience of the king.</td></tr>

